        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 5:27PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 526 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Valatie, or near Chatham, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Barkerville, Rossman, Glendale, Rayville, Riders Mills,
Williamsville, Kinderhook, Brick Tavern, Lenox Dale, Harlemville, The
Center At Lenox, Lorenz Park, West Ghent, Fitchs Wharf, Stearnsville,
Carey Corner, Newton Hook, West Pittsfield, Buckleyville, and New
Lebanon Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central New York.</instruction>
